    "summary": "In \"The Bluest Yellow\", we journey through the vibrant life of Claire, an artist whose work centers around blending seemingly contradictory emotions and colors. The story follows Claire as she navigates personal and professional challenges, using these experiences to fuel her art. Set against the backdrop of a bustling city, Claire's journey reflects her struggle to maintain authenticity in a world that demands conformity. The novel explores themes of identity, creativity, and the balance between commercial success and personal fulfillment.",
